<div id="review_2669872753" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2669872753" />
    <a title="Oleksandr Zholud" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4743119-oleksandr-zholud"><img alt="Oleksandr Zholud" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1506182069p2/4743119.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2669872753?book_show_action=true">Jan 13, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Oleksandr Zholud" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Oleksandr Zholud" href="/user/show/4743119-oleksandr-zholud">Oleksandr Zholud</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2669872753" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10365654952242528372">This is a fantasy novel was a Hugo, Nebula and Locus Award nominee, which I read as a part of Monthly reads in <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/group/show/474371-hugo-nebula-awards-best-novels' rel='nofollow noopener'>Hugo &amp; Nebula Awards: Best Novels</a><br/><br/>This short fantasy novel starts more or less like an ordinary urban/modern fantasy: a 50 year old woman comes to San Francisco. Her name is Martha Macnamara and she wants to meet her [estranged] daughter, who recently called to her for help. In her hotel Martha meets a dark [Chinese?] stranger with immaculate manners and erudition. Almost instantly, she </span>
  <span id="freeText10365654952242528372" style="display:none">This is a fantasy novel was a Hugo, Nebula and Locus Award nominee, which I read as a part of Monthly reads in <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/group/show/474371-hugo-nebula-awards-best-novels" rel="nofollow noopener">Hugo &amp; Nebula Awards: Best Novels</a><br /><br />This short fantasy novel starts more or less like an ordinary urban/modern fantasy: a 50 year old woman comes to San Francisco. Her name is Martha Macnamara and she wants to meet her [estranged] daughter, who recently called to her for help. In her hotel Martha meets a dark [Chinese?] stranger with immaculate manners and erudition. Almost instantly, she is wanted by the bartender, that his guy is a dragon… if you expect that this is followed by sparks and spells, fae or goblins, you are wrong. For the rest of the novel it turns chiefly in a mystery story with a thriller closer to the end.<br /><br />The book has great flowering, poetic prose, rich with descriptions and details. However, the story progression is far from perfect and it is often hard to co-live the story with protagonists.<br /><br />The novel is set in the early 1980s, so old computer geeks can get their nostalgia tinkled a bit, hearing about e.g. 8080 text processor…<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10365654952242528372" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


